Rating: 4
This recipe was fabulous! I took the suggestion of another cook and added 1/4 cup of vinegar to the marinade - also I didn't have any brown sugar on hand, so I substituted 1/4 cup of molasses with 3/4 cup of granulated sugar and it was wonderful. The day of the party I was too busy to make the barbeque sauce and was hoping for the best without it - everyone still raved about the taste of the marinated pork chops - I had marinated them about 28 hours. I can hardly wait to try this recipe on chicken - I think it would be great also. Even if you don't make the sauce, be SURE to make the marinade - you will love it!

